Epoch:0 | TOPIC | Scientist0:The proposal introduces **"Adaptive Loss-Aware Temporal Networks with Distributional Shift Detection"**, a novel framework to improve extreme event detection in imbalanced time series data. It integrates three key components: (1) dynamic loss re-weighting using extreme value theory (e.g., Generalized Pareto Distribution) to emphasize rare events, (2) a dual-path neural architecture separating normal and extreme pattern modeling with attention-based fusion, and (3) online drift detection to trigger model adaptation under non-stationary conditions. The approach moves beyond static rebalancing methods by combining statistical rigor with adaptive deep learning, aiming for real-world impact in high-stakes domains like healthcare, climate, and energy. A pilot application in renewable energy load forecasting is suggested to leverage the team’s expertise in probabilistic modeling and scalable deep learning.
